      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, i just noticed something. the actual answers they gave—the part about listening to the customer and de-escalating—is basically the exact same for both of them. if the core skills and the actual solution they provide are identical, why does the way they talk matter so much for the job? isn't the content of the answer what counts most in customer service?",
