      "content": "i hear you, but i'm looking at it from a different angle. if the job is to help people resolve issues, wouldn't a candidate who speaks more naturally or uses a different dialect actually be better at connecting with a wider, more diverse customer base? it feels like you're saying one way of speaking is \"correct\" and the other is \"weak,\" even though they both expressed the same professional competence. aren't you just assuming that \"professional\" only looks one specific way?",
